-- Asian Stocks Rise as U.S. Jobs Report Boosts Confidence in Global Recovery
-- B y   N i c k   G e n t l e
-- 2010-11-08T00:12:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-08/asian-stocks-rise-as-u-s-jobs-report-boosts-confidence-in-global-recovery.html
Asian stocks rose, with the regional
benchmark index climbing for a sixth day, after the U.S. economy
added more jobs than forecast, boosting confidence in a global
economic recovery.  The MSCI Asia Pacific increased 0.3 percent to 135.18 as of
9:10 a.m. in Tokyo. The index has risen for six days in a row,
the longest winning streak since the eight days to June 21.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at 
 ngentle2@bloomberg.net  